# Calendars

## Packages

Chose to install these via pip: the AUR packages didn't seem well designed, e.g.
the khal one did not specify appropriate python package deps.

- sudo pip install khal "vdirsyncer[google]"

## Setup

- decrypt the vdirsyncer config
  (If you're configuring your own setup, see
  https://vdirsyncer.pimutils.org/en/stable/tutorial.html)
- mkdir ~/calendars
- vdirsyncer discover
- vdirsyncer sync
- configure khal (https://lostpackets.de/khal/configure.html) if necessary
- enable & activate the `systemctl --user` `ical-sync.timer` unit to get
  automatic periodic calendar sync.
